Who can replace the outgoing Vladimir Volfovich Zhirinovsky as leader of the Liberal Democratic Party? His son and deputy Igor Lebedev is clearly not up to par. We need a person who has all the talents of Zhirinovsky: 1) a bright eccentric speaker, 2) a tram hamlo and a brawler, 3) an aggressive quilted jacket, 4) a Jew yelling about "we are for the poor, we are for the g'uss" In addition to Zhirinovsky, only known in Russia one person with all this set of qualities - Vladimir Rudolfovich Solovyov